# Git Workflow for TA-gen_ai_cim

## Repository Layout

This app directory **is** the git repo root (a standalone repository).
There is exactly one remote:

| Remote   | URL                                            | Purpose            |
|----------|------------------------------------------------|--------------------|
| `origin` | https://github.com/mayeack/TA-gen_ai_cim.git   | The TA repo        |

> Historical note: this project once lived as a subtree of a
> `/opt/splunk/etc` monorepo (`5GCoreAnalytics`) pushed via
> `git subtree push` to a `ta-cim` remote. That layout no longer exists —
> do not use subtree commands here.

## Push Workflow

1. Work on a feature branch (`fix/...`, `chore/...`, `feature/...`) —
   never commit directly to `main`.
2. Commit only files under this app; write a real commit message
   (no empty messages).
3. `git push -u origin <branch>` and open a PR against `main`.

## Excluded Files

Never commit:
- `local/` directory and `metadata/local.meta` (instance overrides — this
  checkout is also a live dev Splunk instance)
- `.cursor/mcp.json` and `.claude/settings.local.json` (may contain credentials)
- Large/generated lookup CSVs (see `.gitignore`; the small sample CSVs
  `medadvice_*.csv` and `prompt_injection_training_examples.csv` ARE
  tracked and ship with the app)

## Shared assistant content

Intentionally tracked so the team shares the same context:
- `.cursor/rules/` and `.cursor/skills/` (Cursor)
- `.claude/skills/` and `CLAUDE.md` (Claude Code)

Keep `.cursor/skills/` and `.claude/skills/` in sync when editing either.
